nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|BTW, 3@C is the LOTT bid with a known 9 card club fit. You should always follow LOTT in competition as it is right most of the time. And despite the -150, it actually didn't work out that badly in IMPs (despite the fact that East had a very marginal 2@C bid) since we do make 2@H (110 so only a 1 imp loss). |
